The composition of the House of Representatives continues to change daily as Courts of Appeal giave out different verdicts on 2019 elections. On Tuesday, the House sworn in two members of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) while the All Progressives Congress (APC) got a new member. The members are Chinedu Ogah (APC, Ebonyi), Obinna Chidoka (PDP, Anambra) and Samson Okwu (PDP, Benue). The oath of office was administered by the clerk of the House of Representatives. The House is presently in a closed-door session, following a motion by the Abubakar Fulata. Meanwhile, President Muhammadu Buhari has requested N10.06 billion for Kogi state as repayment for promissory note on work done by the state on behalf the federal government. The letter was read by the Speaker who referred the request to committee on Aid and loans. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.